e":415},"Libertini: ἐποίησε; Ferrua, Korhonen: ἐποίησα",{"loc":417,"note":418},"line 3",{"_":419,"supplied":420},"Libertini, Ferrua: αὐτῇ; Korhonen: ατῇ (i.e. ἐμαυτῇ)",{"_":382,"reason":372},{"loc":422,"note":423},"line 5","Libertini: μετ’ εἰρ[ένῃ] (sic); Ferrua, Korhonen: μετὰ εἰρ[ήνης]",{"type":425,"xml:lang":115,"resp":353,"p":426},"translation","Klaudia Rosskia while alive made (this) for herself and her relatives. In peace.",{"type":425,"xml:lang":275,"resp":335,"p":428},"Klaudia Rosskia mentre era viva realizzò (questo) per lei e per i suoi parenti. In pace.",{"type":430,"p":431},"commentary",{"_":432,"foreign":433,"ref":444},"This Christian epitaph presents the structure with the name of the deceased and the verb  indicating that the deceased, while still alive (participle of ), built the monument (or composed the epigram on the monument) for herself and his relatives (on the same structure in Catania see IG 14.489 =  and Korhonen 2004: 88-89). The clause  is not frequent, more frequently attested is  (see IG 14.556 = ). The gentilicium  reveals the Roman citizenship of the deceased (for other evidence of the gentilicium in inscriptions from Catania, see IG 14.486 = , IG 14.500 = , IG 14.1981 = ).",[434,436,438,440,442],{"_":435,"xml:lang":99},"ποιέω",{"_":437,"xml:lang":99},"ζάω",{"_":439,"xml:lang":99},"μετὰ εἰρήνης",{"_":441,"xml:lang":99},"ἐν εἰρήνῃ",{"_":443,"xml:lang":99},"Ῥωσκία",[445,448,451,454,457],{"_":446,"target":447},"ISic001312","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001312",{"_":449,"target":450},"ISic001375","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001375",{"_":452,"target":453},"ISic001309","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001309",{"_":455,"target":456},"ISic001321","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001321",{"_":458,"target":459},"ISic003252","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic003252",{"type":461,"listBibl":462},"bibliography",[463,506],{"type":351,"bibl":464},[465,473,483,490,498],{"type":466,"n":467,"citedRange":468,"ptr":469,"ref":471},"corpus","IMusCatania","179",{"target":470},"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/2EUC82DH",{"_":472,"target":472},"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028",{"type":474,"n":475,"author":476,"title":475,"date":477,"citedRange":478,"ptr":479,"ref":481},"bulletin","NSA","Libertini","1937","78.i",{"target":480},"http://zotero.org/groups/382445/items/4MCP2PVV",{"_":482,"target":482},"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392",{"author":476,"date":484,"citedRange":485,"ptr":486,"ref":488},"1981","125",{"target":487},"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/ZJ65DX74",{"_":489,"target":489},"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001863",{"author":491,"date":492,"citedRange":493,"ptr":494,"ref":496},"Ferrua","1989","111-112 no.424",{"target":495},"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/759ZXHKQ",{"_":497,"target":497},"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001995",{"author":499,"date":500,"citedRange":501,"ptr":502,"ref":504},"Mercurelli","1938","52-53",{"target":503},"http://zotero.org/groups/382445/items/PHQV78NC",{"_":505,"target":505},"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002228",{"type":507,"bibl":508},"discussion",{"type":466,"n":467,"citedRange":509,"ptr":510,"ref":511},"pp. 88-89",{"target":470},{"_":472,"target":472},[513],{"n":341,"url":89,"height":342,"width":343,"desc":90,"surfaceType":338},{"title":515,"body":516,"divs":517,"images":533},"ISic003283. Epitaph for Klaudia Rosskia","  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003283_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic003283_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003283.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic003283-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"edition\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div\">\u003Ca id=\"al1\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>ΚΛΑΥΔΙΑΡΩΣΣΚ\u003Cbr id=\"al2\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>ΑΖΩΣΑΕΠΟΙΗΣΑ\u003Cbr id=\"al3\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>ΑΤΗΚΑΙΤΟΙΣΕΙ\u003Cbr id=\"al4\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ΔΙΟΙΣ\u003Cbr id=\"al5\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>ΜΕΤΑΕΙΡ[....]\u003Cbr id=\"al6\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>christogram\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text based on photograph\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"lines 1-2\">lines.1-2: \u003Cspan>Libertini: Ῥωσσί|α; Mercurelli, Ferrua, Korhonen: Ῥωσσκ|α\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 2\">line.2: \u003Cspan>Libertini: Ζώηλ(ε); Ferrua, Korhonen: ζῶσα\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 2\">\u003Cspan>Libertini: ἐποίησε; Ferrua, Korhonen: ἐποίησα\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 3\">line.3: \u003Cspan>Libertini, Ferrua: αὐτῇ; Korhonen: ατῇ (i.e. ἐμαυτῇ)\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 5\">line.5: \u003Cspan>Libertini: μετ’ εἰρ[ένῃ] (sic); Ferrua, Korhonen: μετὰ εἰρ[ήνης]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Klaudia Rosskia while alive made (this) for herself and her relatives. In peace.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Klaudia Rosskia mentre era viva realizzò (questo) per lei e per i suoi parenti. In pace.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>This Christian epitaph presents the structure with the name of the deceased and the verb \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ποιέω\u003C/span> indicating that the deceased, while still alive (participle of \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ζάω\u003C/span>), built the monument (or composed the epigram on the monument) for herself and his relatives (on the same structure in Catania see IG 14.489 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001312\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001312\u003C/a> and Korhonen 2004: 88-89). The clause \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">μετὰ εἰρήνης\u003C/span> is not frequent, more frequently attested is \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ἐν εἰρήνῃ\u003C/span> (see IG 14.556 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001375\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001375\u003C/a>). The gentilicium \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Ῥωσκία\u003C/span> reveals the Roman citizenship of the deceased (for other evidence of the gentilicium in inscriptions from Catania, see IG 14.486 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001309\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001309\u003C/a>, IG 14.500 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001321\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001321\u003C/a>, IG 14.1981 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic003252\" target=\"_blank\">ISic003252\u003C/a>).\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>  \u003Cli> 179 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Libertini NSA 1937 78.i \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Libertini 1981 125 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001863\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001863\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Ferrua 1989 111-112 no.424 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001995\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001995\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Mercurelli 1938 52-53 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002228\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002228\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>  \u003Cli> pp. 88-89 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[518,520,522,524,526,528,530],{"id":351,"html":519},"\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div\">\u003Ca id=\"al1\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>ΚΛΑΥΔΙΑΡΩΣΣΚ\u003Cbr id=\"al2\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>ΑΖΩΣΑΕΠΟΙΗΣΑ\u003Cbr id=\"al3\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>ΑΤΗΚΑΙΤΟΙΣΕΙ\u003Cbr id=\"al4\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ΔΙΟΙΣ\u003Cbr id=\"al5\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>ΜΕΤΑΕΙΡ[....]\u003Cbr id=\"al6\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>christogram\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"id":401,"html":521},"\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text based on photograph\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"lines 1-2\">lines.1-2: \u003Cspan>Libertini: Ῥωσσί|α; Mercurelli, Ferrua, Korhonen: Ῥωσσκ|α\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 2\">line.2: \u003Cspan>Libertini: Ζώηλ(ε); Ferrua, Korhonen: ζῶσα\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 2\">\u003Cspan>Libertini: ἐποίησε; Ferrua, Korhonen: ἐποίησα\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 3\">line.3: \u003Cspan>Libertini, Ferrua: αὐτῇ; Korhonen: ατῇ (i.e. ἐμαυτῇ)\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 5\">line.5: \u003Cspan>Libertini: μετ’ εἰρ[ένῃ] (sic); Ferrua, Korhonen: μετὰ εἰρ[ήνης]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>",{"id":425,"html":523},"\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Klaudia Rosskia while alive made (this) for herself and her relatives. In peace.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":425,"html":525},"\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Klaudia Rosskia mentre era viva realizzò (questo) per lei e per i suoi parenti. In pace.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":430,"html":527},"\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>This Christian epitaph presents the structure with the name of the deceased and the verb \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ποιέω\u003C/span> indicating that the deceased, while still alive (participle of \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ζάω\u003C/span>), built the monument (or composed the epigram on the monument) for herself and his relatives (on the same structure in Catania see IG 14.489 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001312\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001312\u003C/a> and Korhonen 2004: 88-89). The clause \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">μετὰ εἰρήνης\u003C/span> is not frequent, more frequently attested is \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ἐν εἰρήνῃ\u003C/span> (see IG 14.556 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001375\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001375\u003C/a>). The gentilicium \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Ῥωσκία\u003C/span> reveals the Roman citizenship of the deceased (for other evidence of the gentilicium in inscriptions from Catania, see IG 14.486 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001309\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001309\u003C/a>, IG 14.500 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001321\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001321\u003C/a>, IG 14.1981 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic003252\" target=\"_blank\">ISic003252\u003C/a>).\u003C/p>  ",{"id":461,"html":529},"\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>  \u003Cli> 179 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Libertini NSA 1937 78.i \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Libertini 1981 125 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001863\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001863\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Ferrua 1989 111-112 no.424 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001995\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001995\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Mercurelli 1938 52-53 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002228\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002228\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>  \u003Cli> pp. 88-89 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003C/ul>  ",{"id":531,"html":532},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. ",[534,536],{"image":89,"thumb":535,"title":90},"ISic003283_tiled-thumb.tif",{"image":346,"thumb":537,"title":90},"ISic003283-thumb.jpg"],"uses":{"params":["slug"]}}]}
